FT  15 AUG 92 / Kabul troops repulse rebels
Troops loyal to the Islamic government in Kabul have repulsed violent
assaults by rebel mujahideen fighters, agencies report from Kabul. However
military chiefs expect another round of fighting as forces loyal to
fundamentalist leader Gulbudddin Hekmatyar prepared to make another bid for
the battle-weary capital.
